org.apache.activemq.core.server.impl

Class AIOFileLockNodeManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.activemq.core.server.NodeManager
      • org.apache.activemq.core.server.impl.FileLockNodeManager
        • org.apache.activemq.core.server.impl.AIOFileLockNodeManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.activemq.core.server.ActiveMQComponent

    public final class AIOFileLockNodeManager
extends FileLockNodeManager
    This is using the ActiveMQ Libaio Native to perform calls to flock on a Linux system. At the current version of RHEL there's a bug on GFS2 and because of that fctl is not functional what will cause issues on Failover over Shared Storage.

    This will provide an alternative to perform locks through our native module until fctl is fixed on Linux.

    https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=678585

    Author:
    clebertsuconic
